78
00:06:40,350 --> 00:06:42,390
You little, gosh!

79
00:06:42,390 --> 00:06:45,020
- Gosh, damn it. 
 - Oh, did you fight like this?

80
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:46,990
- Then I think you would have won. 
 - Excuse me!

81
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:48,840
Could you send him away so I can get some rest?

82
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:51,530
No, no, we're doing perfectly fine here.

83
00:06:51,530 --> 00:06:52,960
Thank you.

84
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:55,310
What's with you? You need rest, so stay still.

85
00:06:55,310 --> 00:06:56,910
Go away while I tell you nicely.

86
00:06:56,910 --> 00:06:58,310
I should be by your side.

87
00:06:58,310 --> 00:07:00,930
Rest, rest. I will protect you by your side.

88
00:07:00,930 --> 00:07:02,770
- It's okay. 
 - Just go.

89
00:07:02,770 --> 00:07:08,170
Ma'am, Joon Hee has chronic renal failure.

90
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:12,210
In the early stages, there are no clear symptoms

91
00:07:12,210 --> 00:07:15,940
and the kidneys slowly lose their capacity to function.

92
00:07:15,940 --> 00:07:20,180
Even when his kidneys lose 70% of functionality, there are no symptoms.

93
00:07:20,180 --> 00:07:23,800
Since the probability of it being hereditary is low, Joon Hee probably didn't know, either.

94
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:27,160
No. He was in pain.

95
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:30,410
It turns out he had been taking pills on his own.

96
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:39,800
While we put him on dialysis,

97
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:43,470
we will put him on the waitlist for a brain-dead patient donor.

98
00:07:52,420 --> 00:08:00,190
Ma'am, the situation is way better on all fronts compared to Joon Young's case.

99
00:08:03,110 --> 00:08:05,080
Don't worry.

100
