152
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:12,070
S-So you had 80% confidence, I see...

153
00:13:12,070 --> 00:13:14,370
Oh, right. This...

154
00:13:16,210 --> 00:13:19,200
Here. Han So Yeon told me to give this to you.

155
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,760
What?

156
00:13:21,810 --> 00:13:23,460
The gym clothes...

157
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:25,420
Gosh, I should've gotten it from her directly!

158
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:28,040
Gosh! What a waste!

159
00:13:28,990 --> 00:13:33,240
Well, it looked like she wanted to give it to you in person, too.

160
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,490
Is my So Yeon doing well?

161
00:13:35,490 --> 00:13:39,800
Oh! And she seemed to worry a lot about Joon Hee.

162
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:46,000
She asked if he was very sick and seemed to want to come to the hospital, getting all teary.

163
00:13:51,310 --> 00:13:54,000
It's a lie. Don't believe him. Han So Yeon wouldn't be getting all teary.

164
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:58,120
Hey, why would it be a lie? That's possible.

165
00:14:00,730 --> 00:14:02,240
You should go back to school.

166
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:04,420
Why leave school early to visit him in the hospital?

167
00:14:04,420 --> 00:14:06,120
Geez...

168
00:14:07,270 --> 00:14:09,870
He hasn't come to school since the day you beat him up.

169
00:14:09,870 --> 00:14:11,620
It's real.

170
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:15,350
- Fuck! Did I beat him up to kill him? 
 - Shit...

171
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:17,020
Gosh...

172
00:14:18,010 --> 00:14:20,270
But why is it so quiet?

173
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:25,270
Why is Pretty Girl here?

174
00:14:25,270 --> 00:14:28,650
Everyone I like is in this class.

175
00:14:28,650 --> 00:14:31,420
If you drink that, you'll die.

176
00:14:33,490 --> 00:14:35,850
I know you can't drink that. I know that much.

177
00:14:35,850 --> 00:14:37,110
I was just joking.

178
00:14:37,110 --> 00:14:39,620
Then why are you salivating?

179
00:14:40,850 --> 00:14:46,410
Soju is 20% ethanol in concentration, while that is over 70%.

180
00:14:46,410 --> 00:14:48,490
You are starting to show off again.

181
00:14:48,490 --> 00:14:52,600
Even that is diluted for use. 100% ethanol passes through cell membranes and—

182
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:54,730
We just won't drink it!

183
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:57,440
Do you know why they say you become a dog when you get drunk?

184
00:14:57,440 --> 00:15:01,470
- Ethyl alcohol, CH3CH2OH... 
 - Goodness.

185
00:15:01,470 --> 00:15:03,760
Gosh, you're amazing. Just amazing.

186
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:06,240
Soon Tak, you take care of this.

187
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:10,530
- Hey! Hey, Go Yoo! Hear me out! 
 - Even if I'm curious, I don't want to hear it.

188
00:15:10,530 --> 00:15:11,720
Take us with you!

189
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:14,420
What a crazy bastard!

190
00:15:14,420 --> 00:15:17,140
It's because the 3D molecular model of alcohol looks like a dog.

191
00:15:17,140 --> 00:15:19,970
- You should know why you become a dog! 
 - That crazy punk!

192
00:15:19,970 --> 00:15:22,650
Soon Tak, let's catch that dog!

193
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:54,310
Hey! Stop following me!

194
00:15:54,310 --> 00:15:55,930
Crazy bastards!

195
00:15:55,930 --> 00:15:57,770
Where are you going?

196
00:15:57,770 --> 00:16:00,720
- Hey, Go Yoo! 
 - Hurry up!

197
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:02,720
Gosh, stop following me!

198
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:04,670
Crazy bastards!

199
00:16:04,670 --> 00:16:06,600
Come over here!

200
00:16:08,110 --> 00:16:09,650
Hey!

201
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:20,670
- Are you tired? 
 - Yeah.

202
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:25,060
So stop showing off so much. That drains a lot of energy.

203
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:04,370
 Here. 

204
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:06,510
 What is it? 

205
00:17:06,510 --> 00:17:07,950
 It's your younger sibling. 

206
00:17:07,950 --> 00:17:09,760
 You should have bought two. 

207
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:11,410
 It will be lonely by itself. 

208
00:17:11,410 --> 00:17:13,410
 If I brought two, they'd ostracize you. 

209
00:17:13,410 --> 00:17:15,030
 You... 

210
00:17:15,030 --> 00:17:16,230
 That's right. 

211
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:19,760
 If there were two, they would be paired up. 

212
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:24,800
 It would make me wonder why I'm not paired up. 

213
00:17:26,940 --> 00:17:28,800
 Dunk. 

214
00:17:29,580 --> 00:17:33,100
 I name it Dunk. 

215
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:38,490
 Dunk? Why would you name my younger sibling? 

216
00:17:38,490 --> 00:17:41,480
 I'm going to name it Tackle! 

217
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:43,520
 Tackle. 

218
00:17:46,270 --> 00:17:48,150
 Tackle. 

219
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:01,560
Dunk...

220
00:18:04,230 --> 00:18:06,580
Answer me.

221
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:15,090
Joon Hee. Joon Hee!

222
00:18:15,090 --> 00:18:19,670
Joon Hee! Joon Hee! Joon Hee...

223
00:18:22,410 --> 00:18:24,520
Hello, please come! Hurry up!

224
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:27,130
Joon Hee. Joon Hee!

225
00:18:35,540 --> 00:18:39,000
Madam Mo, let's get something to eat together.

226
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:42,400
No. I'll eat later.

227
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:47,300
Grandma, don't worry. I'll give Joon Hee my kidney.

228
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:49,840
Wait...

229
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:52,240
What are you talking about?

230
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:57,400
You don't have the right to say no, Mom. If you tell me to choose now, I will choose.

231
00:18:58,120 --> 00:19:00,300
Joon Hee comes before you, Mom.

232
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:10,940
The dialysis isn't effective for Joon Hee! Then transplant is the answer.

233
00:19:10,940 --> 00:19:12,750
You said he has to wait 7 or 8 years for a brain-dead patient donor!

234
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:14,800
Everyone waits without guarantees, too!

235
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:17,920
I can't wait! I feel like I'll die during that time!

236
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:19,970
You still can't. You are an athlete—

237
00:19:19,970 --> 00:19:23,620
I'll live even if I don't do sports, but Joon Hee can't.

238
00:19:25,150 --> 00:19:26,620
I'm done talking. You can't.

239
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:28,890
No need to talk further. It's my body.

240
00:19:28,890 --> 00:19:31,670
You did nothing for me to grow up to this point.

241
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:34,540
- Don't be unreasonable! 
 - I'm not. I thought about it for a long time.

242
00:19:34,540 --> 00:19:37,820
Even if Joon Young were still alive,

243
00:19:39,590 --> 00:19:42,100
I would have still given him my kidney.

244
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:04,510
   
 (Korean blood sausages) 

245
00:20:13,250 --> 00:20:16,080
Don't worry and eat.

246
00:20:16,980 --> 00:20:21,620
Joon Hee and I are not expecting anything of Go Yoo.

247
00:20:22,670 --> 00:20:25,440
You know how we feel, right?

248
00:20:26,590 --> 00:20:29,260
Of course.

249
00:20:29,260 --> 00:20:32,870
If I have to put both of them on operating tables,

250
00:20:32,870 --> 00:20:35,240
I won't be able to endure it.

251
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:37,640
Yes...

252
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:41,800
I'm sorry, Ma'am...

253
00:20:55,250 --> 00:20:57,610
There is no need...

254
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:01,420
for you to feel sorry toward Go Yoo.

255
00:21:02,420 --> 00:21:08,930
A parent should show her child how she lives.

256
00:21:12,690 --> 00:21:16,800
I'm grateful to you, Ma'am.

257
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:20,040
You've pretty much raised my Yoo.

258
00:21:20,040 --> 00:21:25,990
If I didn't have Go Yoo, I don't know if Joon Hee and I would have survived.

259
00:21:25,990 --> 00:21:29,390
After Joon Young died like that,

260
00:21:29,390 --> 00:21:33,740
and Joon Young's mother and father died in a car accident.

261
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:39,970
There was no sound of anyone living at our home,

262
00:21:39,970 --> 00:21:43,160
